OL,3,CUK-wide E.coli outbreak: What do we
OL,4,Cknow so far?
OL,6,FFound in the gut and faeces of many
OL,7,Fanimals, particularly cattle, it can
OL,8,Fbe caught by eating contaminated food,
OL,9,Fraw leafy vegetables or undercooked
OL,10,Fmeat.
OL,12,FA statement from the UKHSA added:
OL,13,F"Based on the wide geographic spread
OL,14,Fof cases, it is most likely that this
OL,15,Foutbreak is linked to a nationally
OL,16,Fdistributed food item or multiple food
OL,17,Fitems."
OL,19,FIt can also be spread by touching
OL,20,Finfected animals or coming into
OL,21,Fcontact with their faeces.
