OL,3,CUK-wide E.coli outbreak: What do we
OL,4,Cknow so far?
OL,6,FSome strains produce toxins that can
OL,7,Fmake people very ill, such as Stec.
OL,8,FPeople infected with Stec can suffer
OL,9,Fdiarrhoea, and about 50% of cases have
OL,10,Fbloody diarrhoea.
OL,12,FOther symptoms include stomach cramps
OL,13,Fand fever. Symptoms can last up to two
OL,14,Fweeks in uncomplicated cases.
OL,16,FSome patients, mainly children, may
OL,17,Fdevelop haemolytic uraemic syndrome
OL,18,F(HUS) which is a serious life-
OL,19,Fthreatening condition resulting in
OL,20,Fkidney failure.
